    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_axodyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>axodyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>axost</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>axwadun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>axwast</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>axust</orth></form></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>вкушать</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>to taste</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(специально о младшем члене семьи):
                        </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(of a younger family member):
                        </note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>делать предусмотренный обычаем первый кус после молитвы старшего</q>
                    </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(специально о младшем члене семьи):
                        </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(of a younger family member):
                        </note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>according to custom, make the first bite after the elder's prayer</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>axodgæ ʒy kænyn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>я из него (бокала) отведаю</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Iʼll taste from it (glass)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>227</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>næ cænxæ æma nin næ kærʒin isaxwadæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вкуси нашей соли и хлеба</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>taste our salt and bread</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><biblScope>from a manuscript by %sG. Kokiev%s</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>læppū, rawaj, acaxod, mæ xūr</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мальчик, подойди, отведай, мое солнышко</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>boy, come and taste, my sunshine</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>læqwæn… niwazæn rask’afta…, mink’i æj raaxusta, wædta æj fæstæmæ
                            ravardta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>юноша схватил кубок, немного его отведал, а затем вернул обратно</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the young man grabbed the goblet, tasted it a little, and then placed
                                it back</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ærtæ sæwmi imæ ænaxustæj racæwuncæ… ostitæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>три утра выходят к нему женщины, не вкусив пищи</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>three mornings women come out to him without having tasted food</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">— „Смайли взял wælībæx (пирог) с куском шашлыка в
                    одну руку и рог с аракой в другую, поднялся и стал молиться… «Acaxod!» —
                    обратился ко мне Смайли, когда кончил молитву. Я знал, что значит acaxod. Это
                    значило — подойти и взять wæIībæx и кусок шашлыка, откусить от них немного,
                    потом отпить глоток араки…“ (<bibl><biblScope>Инал %sКануков%s. В осетинском
                            ауле. Осетинские рассказы, М., 1952, стр. 46</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">— “Smaili took wælībæx (pie) with a piece of
                    barbecue in one hand and a horn with araka in the other, got up and began to
                    pray… ʽAcaxod!ʼ Smaili turned to me when he finished his prayer. I knew what
                    acaxod meant. It meant to come up and take wæIībæx and a piece of barbecue, bite
                    off a little, then take a sip of araka…” (<bibl><biblScope>Inal %sKanukov%s.
                            In the Ossetian village. Ossetian stories, Moscow, 1952, p.
                            46</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*a-hvad-</w></mentioned>. Старое сращение преверба <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_a-"/> ‘вкушать’ с основой %i*hvad-%i, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="iir"><lang/>
                        <w>*svad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>вкушать</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср.<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>svăd-</w>
                        <gloss><q>лакомиться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svā́datē, ā-svādáyati</w>
                        <gloss><q>вкушать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>лакомиться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svādú-</w>
                        <gloss><q>сладкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svā́da-</w>
                        <gloss><q>вкус</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hvāsta-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (прош.
                            причастие)</note>
                        <gloss><q>сделанный вкусным</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>hudəma-</w>
                        <gloss><q>сладость</q></gloss></mentioned>; сюда же относят <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>vād</w>
                        <gloss><q>соль</q></gloss></mentioned> (← ‘приправа’), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>xō</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>xvand</w>
                        <gloss><q>сладость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>xvāī, xvā</w>
                        <gloss><q>вкус</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>xvāstan</w>
                        <gloss><q>желать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>110, 111</biblScope></bibl>), а вне
                    арийских языков — <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>súdyti</w>
                        <gloss><q>приправлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>swēte</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>sweet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>süss</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>suavis</w>
                        <gloss><q>сладкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἤδομαι</w>
                        <gloss><q>блаженствовать</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 516
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 516
                            ff.</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 150</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26,
                            58</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*a-hvad-</w></mentioned>. Old fusion of the preverb <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_a-"/> ‘taste’ with the stem %i*hvad-%i, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="iir"><lang/>
                        <w>*svad-</w>
                        <gloss><q>taste</q></gloss></mentioned>, cf.<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>svăd-</w>
                        <gloss><q>feast on</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svā́datē, ā-svādáyati</w>
                        <gloss><q>taste</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>feast on</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svādú-</w>
                        <gloss><q>sweet</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>svā́da-</w>
                        <gloss><q>taste (n.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hvāsta-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (past
                            participle)</note>
                        <gloss><q>made tasty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>hudəma-</w>
                        <gloss><q>sweetness</q></gloss></mentioned>; here too, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>vād</w>
                        <gloss><q>salt</q></gloss></mentioned> (← ‘condiment’), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>xō</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>xvand</w>
                        <gloss><q>sweetness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>xvāī, xvā</w>
                        <gloss><q>taste (n.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>xvāstan</w>
                        <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>110, 111</biblScope></bibl>), and
                    outside the Aryan languages — <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>súdyti</w>
                        <gloss><q>spice (v)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>swēte</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>sweet</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>süss</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>suavis</w>
                        <gloss><q>sweet</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἤδομαι</w>
                        <gloss><q>bliss</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 516
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 516
                            ff.</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 150</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26,
                            58</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
